&lt;Dowa Mining Co Ltd> said it will startcommercial production of gold, copper, lead and zinc from itsNurukawa Mine in northern Japan in April.    A company spokesman said the mine's monthly output isexpected to consist of 1,300 tonnes of gold ore and 3,700 ofblack ore, which consists of copper, lead and zinc ores.    A company survey shows the gold ore contains up to 13.3grams of gold per tonne, he said.    Proven gold ore reserves amount to 50,000 tonnes whileestimated reserves of gold and black ores total one mln tonnes,he added. REUTER&#3;